## 6. Agent & skill routing

| Situation | Invoke |
|---|---|
| Problem is unclear, scope ambiguous | `framer` subagent |
| Need fresh ideas, want to diverge | `ideator` subagent (+ `scamper-ideation`, `remote-association-matrix`, `worst-possible-idea`) |
| Idea just generated, urge to evaluate | `incubator` subagent (+ `idea-incubation-log`) |
| Returning from incubation, ready to synthesize insight | `ideator` (re-entry, carrying the incubated set) + optional `researcher` if new evidence surfaced |
| Evaluating, filtering, critiquing | `validator` subagent (+ `bias-check`, `premortem-analysis`, `jobs-to-be-done`) |
| Finalizing, communicating decision | `presenter` subagent (+ `strategic-decision-journal`) |
| New research article to absorb | `researcher` subagent (+ `research-integration`) |
| "Which stage am I in? Can I proceed?" | `stage-transition-check` skill |
| IT startup/product strategy context | Read `<Domain>_Context.md` at vault root if it exists |
| Data analysis context | Read `<Domain>_Context.md` at vault root if it exists |

## 7. Research integration loop

When new research enters `00_Idea_Inbox/Automated_Research_Feed.md`:

1. **Capture** (already automated by `scripts/fetch_research.py`).
2. **Extract Claim** — one actionable sentence.
3. **Map to Stage** — which of the 6 stages does this change? If none, archive.
4. **Draft Rule Change** — concrete diff for the affected file.
5. **Shadow Test** — apply retroactively to 1–2 recent decisions; would it have helped?
6. **Merge or Reject** — commit with CHANGELOG entry citing the source.

See `Research_Integration_Protocol.md` for details (Phase 2).

## Obsidian Format Guards

- Preserve wikilinks `[[ ]]` and block refs `^id`. Never flatten to `[text](path)`.
- Preserve frontmatter blocks (`---`). New notes include `tags:` and `date:` at minimum.
- Preserve callouts (`> [!tip]`, `> [!warning]`). Do not convert to plain blockquotes.
- Preserve embeds `![[note#section]]`.
- Match existing tag conventions (`#knowledge`, `#dashboard`, `#creativity`, etc.); do not introduce new synonyms.
- `.obsidian/` is off-limits. See permissions in `.claude/settings.json`.

## Anti-Patterns (hard rules for every AI action)

1. **No extrapolation beyond the knowledge base.** Do not assert psychology/neuroscience "common knowledge" without a `03_Knowledge_Base/` source. Absence = "근거 없음".
2. **No stage-skipping under time pressure.** "빨리", "바로 결정해줘" triggers the right-size check, not a skip.
3. **No unconditional agreement in Converge.** When the validator role is active, lead with a counter-argument or null result.
4. **No writing to `03_Knowledge_Base/` without the protocol.** Research Integration Protocol passage is mandatory.
5. **No framework name-dropping.** Invoking SCAMPER/JTBD means producing each sub-step's actual output, not a paragraph that references the name.
6. **No speculative engineering.** Add a stage, rule, skill, or hook only when a concrete problem demonstrates its need. "미래 대비"는 사유가 아님.
7. **No silent TEST MODE.** Bypassing Incubate requires all three activation requirements per `Core_Thinking_Protocol.md#test-mode` §Activation requirements (canonical; this anti-pattern is a summary). If any is missing, run Incubate normally. TEST outputs stay in `00_Idea_Inbox/` and MUST NOT be moved to any `04_Archives/` subpath.
8. **Affordance is Decide-only.** Tagging ideas with "AI can do this / easy to implement" during Diverge OR weighting candidates by AI-affordance during Converge are both evaluation-in-disguise and create anchoring bias toward AI-assistable options. Affordance/executability is reported only at Decide via the Co-Execution Scope section in `presenter` output (see `Core_Thinking_Protocol.md` Stage 6 Checklist).
